**Title:** COM - RFID/NFC Community

**Website:** [saintcon.org/com-rfid-nfc-community/](https://saintcon.org/com-rfid-nfc-community/)

**Community Overview:**
- Hosted by: Iceman and Gobo42
- Focus: Education on RFID/NFC technology, tools, and techniques for reading, storing, replaying, sniffing, scanning, and securing RFID systems.

**Learning Opportunities:**
- Participants can engage in hands-on activities with zero prior knowledge.
- Tools introduced:
  - Proxmark3
  - Chameleon Ultra
  - Flipper Zero
- Areas covered:
  - Basics of RFID/NFC technology
  - Evaluating vulnerabilities
  - Practical challenges designed as CTF (Capture The Flag) exercises

**Hours of Operation:**
- **Monday:** Closed
- **Tuesday:** 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday:** 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Thursday:** 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Friday:** 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM

**What to Bring:** (optional)
- Laptop
- RFID cards for investigation
- RFID reading devices (Proxmark3, Chameleon Ultra, Flipper Zero)

**Additional Offerings:**
- MiniBadge available with details announced at the booth.
- Desktop wallpapers available for download from the community.

**Meta Information:**
- **Open Graph Description:** RFID/NFC can be a difficult technology to understand. Come learn how! Experience learning about short-range communication through RFID and explore various reading techniques.
- **Image:** ![RFID Image](http://www.saintcon.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/RFID-2023_5K_Wallpaper.png)

